      "content": "The \"hidden\" or \"unavailable\" error can be a bit misleading, but it's likely due to the browser's layout engine struggling to render the background color. This can happen when the browser is trying to calculate the layout of the element, and it's encountering a style that's causing it to stall. It's almost like the browser is saying, \"I'm not sure how to render this, so I'm hiding it.\"\n\nIn some cases, this can be a result of the browser's default text color being set to a similar shade of green, which can cause the background color to be ignored. You can try setting the text color to a different value, like `color: #FFFFFF;`, to see if that resolves the issue. Alternatively, you can try using the `box-shadow` property to create a semi-transparent overlay on the text, which can help the browser render the background color correctly.",
